tive. Drawing on pioneering empirical research in countries as diverse as Britain, Uganda, Norway, Pakistan, India, South Korea and China, it outlines core principles that can aid policy makers in policy development. In so doing, it provides the foundation for a shift in policy learning on a global scale and bridges the traditional distinctions between North and South, and high-, middle- and low-income countries. This will help students, academics and policy makers better understand the reasons for the varying effectiveness of anti-poverty policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPovertyxPreventionxGovernment policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aChase, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoudhry, Sohail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGubrium, Erika K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGubrium, Erika K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJo, Yongmie Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKyomuhendo, Grace Bantebya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLødemel, Ivar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLødemel, Ivar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMathew, Leemamol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMwiine, Amon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPellissery, Sony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPellissery, Sony, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWalker, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYan, Ming, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab